%N A003423 a(n) = a(n-1)^2 - 2, with a(0) = 6.
%C A003423 If x is either of the roots of x^2 - 6*x + 1 = 0 (i.e., x = 3 +- 2*sqrt(2)), then x^(2^n) + 1 = a(n)*x^(2^(n-1)). For example, x^8 + 1 = 1154*x^4. - _James East_, Oct 05 2018
